  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is the weather better in Sydney than Auckland?",
  "response": "The concept of \"better\" weather is subjective and depends on what you consider ideal. Here's a comparison of the weather in Sydney, Australia, and Auckland, New Zealand:\n\n### Sydney Weather:\n- **Climate**: Sydney has a temperate climate with warm summers and mild winters.\n- **Summer (December to February)**: Average highs around 26-30\u00b0C (79-86\u00b0F), with occasional heatwaves pushing temperatures above 35\u00b0C (95\u00b0F).\n- **Winter (June to August)**: Average highs around 16-18\u00b0C (61-64\u00b0F), with lows around 8-10\u00b0C (46-50\u00b0F). Frost is rare.\n- **Rainfall**: Sydney gets around 1214 mm of rain annually, spread fairly evenly throughout the year, though it can be more humid in the summer.\n- **Sunshine**: Sydney enjoys around 2,600 hours of sunshine per year.\n\n### Auckland Weather:\n- **Climate**: Auckland has a subtropical climate with warm, humid summers and mild, damp winters.\n- **Summer (December to February)**: Average highs around 23-25\u00b0C (73-77\u00b0F), with occasional highs above 30\u00b0C (86\u00b0F).\n- **Winter (June to August)**: Average highs around 14-16\u00b0C (57-61\u00b0F), with lows around 7-9\u00b0C (45-48\u00b0F). Frost is also rare but can occur.\n- **Rainfall**: Auckland receives about 1245 mm of rain annually, with rain distributed throughout the year, though it can be more frequent in winter.\n- **Sunshine**: Auckland gets around 2,050 hours of sunshine per year.\n\n### Comparison:\n- **Temperature**: Sydney generally experiences higher temperatures in summer and slightly warmer winters.\n- **Rainfall**: Both cities receive similar amounts of rain, though Auckland's rain can be more frequent and persistent.\n- **Sunshine**: Sydney enjoys more sunshine hours annually.\n- **Humidity**: Auckland tends to be more humid year-round.\n\nIf you prefer warmer and sunnier conditions, you might find Sydney's weather more appealing. However, if you enjoy milder temperatures and don't mind a bit more humidity and rain, Auckland could be more to your liking.",
